        <h2>About OncologyIT</h2>
        <p>OncologyIT is an independent platform for analysis and education at the intersection of oncology, health IT, and artificial intelligence. It exists because the people making decisions about AI in cancer care — oncologists, health IT leaders, practice administrators — deserve analysis from someone who has operated in all three worlds.</p>

        <h2>About the Author</h2>
        <p>I'm a medical oncologist with over 30 years of clinical experience. I was among the early adopters of electronic medical records — implementing iKnowMed when most practices were still on paper — and have watched the full arc of health IT from early EMR adoption through the current wave of agentic AI.</p>

        <p>I hold an MIT Sloan AI Healthcare Executive Certificate and serve as CEO of Nexgen Precision, where we're building AI-native infrastructure for oncology practices.</p>

        <p>My work sits at a specific intersection: I'm a clinician who builds technology, not a technologist who advises clinicians. That distinction matters when the stakes are patient outcomes.</p>

        <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weekly writing</strong> — Independent analysis on AI policy, health IT shifts, and the systems reshaping oncology.</li>
          <li><strong>The OncoTech AI Podcast</strong> — Deep-dive conversations on clinical AI deployment, regulatory dynamics, and infrastructure decisions.</li>
          <li><strong>Toolkit &amp; Resources</strong> — Curated books, tools, frameworks, and learning paths for clinical leaders navigating the AI transition.</li>
          <li><strong>AI Foundations Certification</strong> — A formal course covering AI fundamentals through the lens of healthcare and oncology.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Philosophy</h2>
        <p>This platform is vendor-independent. No sponsored content, no affiliate-driven recommendations, no venture capital influence. The analysis is shaped by clinical reality, not commercial interest.</p>

        <p>I write with a specific reader in mind: the oncologist who is skeptical of hype but knows something fundamental is changing, and wants to understand it clearly enough to act on it.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>For professional inquiries, speaking engagements, or collaboration, connect with me on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/jiveshsharma">LinkedIn</a>.</p>
      </div>
